HEADWORD: Salimeter
<hw>Sal*im"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sal</ets> salt + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for
measuring the amount of salt present in any given solution.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>salometer</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

